{
  "page": "Tarber",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\">Tarber</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\"></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Crownlands\" title=\"Crownlands\">Crownlands</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Book</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings\" title=\"A Clash of Kings\">A Clash of Kings</a></i> (appears)</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Tarber</b> is one of the orphan boys <a href=\"/index.php/Yoren\" title=\"Yoren\">Yoren</a> recruits for the <a href=\"/index.php/Night%E2%80%99s_Watch\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Night’s Watch\">Night’s Watch</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/King%E2%80%99s_Landing\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"King’s Landing\">King’s Landing</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racokappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racokappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> \n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Tarber&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Clash_of_Kings\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Tarber&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Clash of Kings\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Tarber_Cutjack_Kurz_Koss_and_Reysen_(ACoK_Comic).jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/0/00/Tarber_Cutjack_Kurz_Koss_and_Reysen_%28ACoK_Comic%29.jpg/350px-Tarber_Cutjack_Kurz_Koss_and_Reysen_%28ACoK_Comic%29.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"150\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/0/00/Tarber_Cutjack_Kurz_Koss_and_Reysen_%28ACoK_Comic%29.jpg/525px-Tarber_Cutjack_Kurz_Koss_and_Reysen_%28ACoK_Comic%29.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/0/00/Tarber_Cutjack_Kurz_Koss_and_Reysen_%28ACoK_Comic%29.jpg/700px-Tarber_Cutjack_Kurz_Koss_and_Reysen_%28ACoK_Comic%29.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Tarber_Cutjack_Kurz_Koss_and_Reysen_(ACoK_Comic).jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Tarber, <a href=\"/index.php/Cutjack\" title=\"Cutjack\">Cutjack</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Kurz\" title=\"Kurz\">Kurz</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Koss\" title=\"Koss\">Koss</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Reysen\" title=\"Reysen\">Reysen</a> resist the Gold Cloaks by Mel Rubi</div></div></div>\n<p>As one of <a href=\"/index.php/Yoren\" title=\"Yoren\">Yoren</a>'s recruits, Tarber travels north from <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a>. When one of their band, <a href=\"/index.php/Praed\" title=\"Praed\">Praed</a>, dies and is buried along the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsroad\" title=\"Kingsroad\">kingsroad</a>, Tarber drops a handful of acorns on the body, so that an <a href=\"/index.php/Oak\" title=\"Oak\">oak</a> might grow to mark the grave.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok5.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok5.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>That evening, the band arrives at an inn with a bathhouse and Tarber joins those who want to take a bath. He is the first to join Yoren in his resistance against the men of the <a href=\"/index.php/City_Watch_of_King%E2%80%99s_Landing\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"City Watch of King’s Landing\">City Watch of King’s Landing</a> who arrive at the inn to arrest <a href=\"/index.php/Gendry\" title=\"Gendry\">Gendry</a>. Tarber picks up a pitchfork for a weapon. The men of the City Watch eventually retreat without further violence.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok5.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok5.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The group avoids the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsroad\" title=\"Kingsroad\">kingsroad</a> following this encounter and instead moves north along the eastern side of <a href=\"/index.php/Gods_Eye_river\" title=\"Gods Eye river\">the river</a> running south from the <a href=\"/index.php/Gods_Eye\" title=\"Gods Eye\">Gods Eye</a>. When they come across an abandoned cottage, Tarber finds a garden in the backyard where they pull some onions and radishes. At <a href=\"/index.php/Gods_Eye_town\" title=\"Gods Eye town\">a town</a> on the southern shore of the Gods Eye, they spend the night in the town's holdfast, where Yoren assigns Tarber, <a href=\"/index.php/Kurz\" title=\"Kurz\">Kurz</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Cutjack\" title=\"Cutjack\">Cutjack</a> the task of holding vigil from on high at the towerhouse of the town.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The whole town is burned down that night by men under the command of Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Amory_Lorch\" title=\"Amory Lorch\">Amory Lorch</a>. Kurz manages to warn the rest of the band with his hunting horn, but the holdfast is attacked and taken over nonetheless and most of the group killed.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> However, Lorch's men cannot put the towerhouse on fire and they have no patience to starve out the three up there. They reunited with <a href=\"/index.php/Arya_Stark\" title=\"Arya Stark\">Arry</a> and others who escaped the holdfast via a tunnel.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok19.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok19.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> The injured <a href=\"/index.php/Kurz\" title=\"Kurz\">Kurz</a> dies from an infection of his wound, after which Tarber and Cutjack take everything of value and abandon the other survivors.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok19.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok19.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Tarber&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\" style=\"-webkit-column-width:200px; -moz-column-width:200px; column-width:200px; -webkit-column-count:2; -moz-column-count:2; column-count:2;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Racokappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racokappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings\" title=\"A Clash of Kings\">A Clash of Kings</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings-Appendix\" title=\"A Clash of Kings-Appendix\">Appendix</a>.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Racok5.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok5.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">2.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok5.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\">2.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings\" title=\"A Clash of Kings\">A Clash of Kings</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings-Chapter_5\" title=\"A Clash of Kings-Chapter 5\">Chapter 5</a>, Arya II.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Racok14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">3.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\">3.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings\" title=\"A Clash of Kings\">A Clash of Kings</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings-Chapter_14\" title=\"A Clash of Kings-Chapter 14\">Chapter 14</a>, Arya IV.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Racok19.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok19.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\">4.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok19.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\">4.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings\" title=\"A Clash of Kings\">A Clash of Kings</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings-Chapter_19\" title=\"A Clash of Kings-Chapter 19\">Chapter 19</a>, Arya V.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260405035742\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.088 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.408 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 645/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 10580/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 4796/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 309/2097152 b